<subSubSection id="43EB6555F72A2327FCACFEC24880B4FA" pageId="3" pageNumber="102" type="distribution">
<caption id="5F8E6656F72A2327FCACFEC24880B4FA" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6627847" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6627847" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6627847/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="102" targetBox="[164,757,305,720]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="0B4E36DEF72A2327FCACFEC24880B4FA" blockId="3.[779,1371,307,726]" pageId="3" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="3985EACCF72A2327FCACFEC248ABB474" bold="true" box="[780,956,307,332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="102">Distribution.</emphasis>
E Brazilian Amazon, limited in N by Amazon River, in W by Rio Madeira, and in E by Rio Xingu; S limit is unknown.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="43EB6555F72A2327FCACFE3948A5B673" pageId="3" pageNumber="102" type="description">
<paragraph id="0B4E36DEF72A2327FCACFE394E4DB7EE" blockId="3.[779,1371,307,726]" pageId="3" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="3985EACCF72A2327FCACFE394F07B4D1" bold="true" box="[780,1040,456,489]" pageId="3" pageNumber="102">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
No specific data are available. Dorsal color of the Xingu Silky Anteater is gray, rump is yellow, venter is pale yellowish, and legs and tail are gray. Dorsalstripe is evident, and ventral stripe is indistinct and irregular. Fronto-nasal region of skull is not depressed, giving a
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0B4E36DEF72A2327FF07FD1148A5B673" blockId="3.[164,1370,736,1238]" pageId="3" pageNumber="102">straight profile. External aperture of ear is directed laterally. Naso-maxillary sutures are about parallel to each other, with wide fronto-maxillary suture. Fronto-parietalis triangular, and pterygoid bone overlaps tympanic bulla.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
